HEADWORD: Rascally
<hw>Ras"cal*ly</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧s"k⟦ait⟧l*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Like a rascal; trickish or dishonest; base; worthless; -- often in
humorous disparagement, without implication of dishonesty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our <qex>rascally</qex> porter is fallen fast asleep.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rase</ent>⟦br⟧
